      passage: `While researching, a student has taken the following notes:<br>&bull; A supercontinent is a single landmass made up of most or all of Earth's continents.<br>&bull; Supercontinents form and break apart in a cycle.<br>&bull; The supercontinent Vaalbara formed about 3.6 billion years ago.<br>&bull; The supercontinent Euramerica formed about 300 million years ago.`,
